sses might be included in the native image, I need to be cautious with how code paths are referenced at runtime. I'll explore maintaining current tests while adding a specific test for the `BeanCopier` class initialization.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating class loading options**\\n\\nI'm considering whether we can catch `ClassNotFoundException`. The rule mentions that for dynamic class loading in a native image, we should only catch an `Error`, without mentioning checked exceptions. It could be better to avoid dynamic loading altogether in native scenarios because we can't guard against it. Using a generated proxy class might help, and it seems that direct reflection or dynamic loading in tests is prohibited, which makes me think about alternatives. I could try using `Class.forName()` with the appropriate class loader.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_vDSTV1vGIuwX9rCpcUeVrL53|fc_0969d36bc46c10920169f5ac3e716481a2beb419e442e5d1a7", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "javap -classpath /home/vjovanov/.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1/cglib/cglib-nodep/2.2.2/d456bb230c70c0b95c76fb28e429d42f275941/cglib-nodep-2.2.2.jar -c -p -l 'net.sf.cglib.beans.BeanCopier$Generator' | tail -80"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 4136, "output": 1289, "cacheRead": 20480, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 25905, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777708074470, "responseId": "resp_0969d36bc46c10920169f5ac2ae8c881a291e64f7e649d9658"}}
